    {
      "id": "PopularPost43749",
      "post_content": "To answer your question Gezus82.\n  \n   \nDebtors knell's ability is on the stack, not the creature your trying to resurect. According to the following from the MTG comprensive rule book, a spell is defined as:\n  \n   \n111.1. A spell is a card on the stack. As the first step of being cast (see rule 601, \u201cCasting Spells\u201d), the card becomes a spell and is moved to the top of the stack from the zone it was in, which is usually its owner\u2019s hand. (See rule 405, \u201cStack.\u201d) A spell remains on the stack as a spell until it resolves (see rule 608, \u201cResolving Spells and Abilities\u201d), is countered (see rule 701.5), or otherwise leaves the stack. For more information, see section 6, \u201cSpells, Abilities, and Effects.\u201d\n  \n   \nErgo, debtors knell won't help you use Deathbringer Liege's \"whenever you play a spell\" abilitys. Which really sucks for me since I use White black reserection. I recomend bouncing your cheap creatures in play or graveyard to get the effect your after. Good luck.",
      "posted_by": "medomai",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost43749\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">To answer your question Gezus82.\r<br/> <br/>Debtors knell's <u>ability</u> is on the stack, not the creature your trying to resurect. According to the following from the MTG comprensive rule book, a spell is defined as:\r<br/> <br/>111.1. A spell is a card on the stack. As the first step of being cast (see rule 601, \u201cCasting Spells\u201d), the card becomes a spell and is moved to the top of the stack from the zone it was in, which is usually its owner\u2019s hand. (See rule 405, \u201cStack.\u201d) A spell remains on the stack as a spell until it resolves (see rule 608, \u201cResolving Spells and Abilities\u201d), is countered (see rule 701.5), or otherwise leaves the stack. For more information, see section 6, \u201cSpells, Abilities, and Effects.\u201d\r<br/> <br/>Ergo, debtors knell won't help you use Deathbringer Liege's \"whenever you play a spell\" abilitys. Which really sucks for me since I use White black reserection. I recomend bouncing your cheap creatures in play or graveyard to get the effect your after. Good luck.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '43749'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy21882\">medomai</span>\r\n  